 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.3.3","title":"task(opentui-import IR): Build normalization passes (desugaring, canonical ordering, dead semantic pruning)","description":"Objective: Implement normalization pass pipeline to simplify semantically equivalent IR variants into canonical forms for stable translation and comparison.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n1. Passes are idempotent and order-stable.\\n2. Canonical ordering is explicit for nodes, edges, and metadata maps.\\n3. Dead semantic pruning never removes behaviorally observable intent.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:02.571939410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T05:21:43.476315176Z","closed_at":"2026-02-25T05:21:43.476295980Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ir","normalization","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:02.571939410Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:19.491175855Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.3.4","title":"task(opentui-import IR): Infer layout, focus, and interaction intent graphs","description":"Objective: Infer higher-level intent graphs (layout constraints, focus traversal, interaction clusters) needed for high-quality FrankenTUI generation beyond syntax-level translation.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n1. Inference outputs confidence-scored intents with explainable evidence.\\n2. Ambiguous intent paths are preserved as alternatives for planner decisions.\\n3. Focus and interaction graphs are compatible with ftui-runtime event model.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:03.128587342Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T05:42:21.483370551Z","closed_at":"2026-02-25T05:42:21.483352317Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inference","ir","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:03.128587342Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:19.960070892Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.3.5","title":"task(opentui-import IR): Canonicalize effects and async boundaries into deterministic command/subscription model","description":"Objective: Convert extracted effect semantics into a deterministic IR form aligned with FrankenTUI command/subscription execution boundaries.\\n\\nAcceptance criteria:\\n1. Effect ordering and cancellation boundaries are explicit.\\n2. Retry/backoff/timer semantics are represented without hidden side channels.\\n3. Model supports deterministic replay and certification diffing.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:03.717644198Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T05:46:48.300938868Z","closed_at":"2026-02-25T05:46:48.300917798Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["effects","ir","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:30:03.717644198Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:37:20.420080975Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
